Para calcular la clasificación global de estrellas y el desglose porcentual por estrella, no utilizamos un promedio simple. D. T. Perez
4,0 de 5 estrellas Caja para ordenar tus raspberrys
Revisado en España el 13 de octubre de 2020
Compra verificada
Compre esta caja ya que tenía un par de raspberry's en cajas separadas y quería un poco de orden.

Vale sin problemas para la Pi 3 y 4, ya que es completamente abierta por los lados.

Trae unos ventiladores adaptados para las raspberry's y no son muy ruidosos. La caja trae también unos disipadores, pero en mi caso no he tenido que usarlos. Incluye destornillador.

Lo único que me ha sido un poco más complicado ha sido que el sistema para anclar las raspberrys a las plataformas usa unos tornillos que se pueden complicar de poner, por lo pequeños que son y el poco espacio que hay pero con el destornillador imantado se puede hacer con un poco de paciencia.

Otro punto negativo es que las instrucciones no valen para nada ya que las imágenes son tan pequeñas que no se ve nada.

Paul
5,0 de 5 estrellas Certainly is compatible with Raspberry pi 4+
Revisado en Reino Unido el 12 de julio de 2019
Compra verificada
I went looking for cases for the pi 4, and separately for heatsinks and a fan. This package includes everything in 1 little box. No need to hunt around for different sets, which is a huge bonus.

This DOES work for the new Pi 4 4GB model, which was recently released, but I'll put 1 minor issue with this set (let's be honest, I'm just nit-picking here), I had to use one of the spare large heatsinks (designated for the CPU) for the memory, as the smaller one barely covers 1/3 of the memory.

Stress testing the CPU, I hit 53C max, which is far lower than running without one, so it has most certainly done its job.

For my old Pi 3, it's perfect, all the heatsinks are adequate and the included fan keeps things nice and cool.

The only MINOR suggestion I'd make to update this box is to include 4 more "cpu" heatsinks to cover the CPU & ram chip (for the pi 4 4GB version). I'm not sure if the 2 or 1 gig versions have a large ram chip, so I can't comment on that. If you're not using all 4 racks, the spares are more than adequate to cover everything that's needed.

Amazon Customer
5,0 de 5 estrellas Watch the clearance of the fan bolts from the underside of the Pi baord.
Revisado en Reino Unido el 23 de mayo de 2020
Compra verificada
A few minor issues with this product.

1) Instructions are a bit unclear in poor English - how difficult can it be to get an English speaker to review the instructions prior to printing?
2) The connectors for the fan power are a bit flimsy and you need to be careful when connecting them.
3) Fan Fixing Bolts: The ends of the bolts are dangerously close to the underside of the Pi above them. The instructions are very clear about this but shorter bolts would be better.

Other than that this is a good value product and seems to work well once assembled. Works equally well for Pi 3B and 4B in the same case. Fans are not too noisy however l'd be interested to see how long they last if run 24x7x365. They do the job and reduced the CPU temp of my Pi's by nearly 30 degC.

I'll be buying another one.
